&lt;p&gt;Our campaign digital strategy team plays a vital role in driving meaningful change, working on projects that elevate causes and create lasting impact. From competitive congressional campaigns to statewide races and national PACs, we craft digital strategies that mobilize support, increase visibility, and generate crucial funding. In 2025, we will actively begin hiring for the 2025-2026 cycle, focusing on full-time roles in digital fundraising, media, and creative. Interested applicants should indicate their preference for a particular type of role in their materials.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience, Skills and Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While skills and experiences can range, most successful candidates at BCom possess the following attributes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience raising money online for a political or issue-based campaign, nonprofit or democrat allied organization or agency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent customer service and relationship building skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptable, communicative, and attentive to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong writing, editing, and proofreading abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with common CRMs and ability to learn new digital tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of media that make up the digital ecosystem (fundraising, ads, web, texting, social, etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong familiarity and interest with the current political landscape&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage several projects at once, from assignment to delivery in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using data and projections to forecast fundraising performance and inform strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a dynamic remote environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manager/director positions must have experience leading successful teams and consistently achieving client goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Areas of Responsibility&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following set of responsibilities are general to the work we do at BCom. &lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will vary depending on job and experience levels.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execution and delegation of deliverables for fundraising, digital advertising, social media, and/or other digital projects as required. This can include:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of client email + social content calendars&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drafting compelling content asking for grassroots donations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Code and segment emails to targeted universes on email CRM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review performance and optimize program based on performance data&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate successes to client and maintain a positive client relationship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work as part of a team on additional accounts to handle tasks as assigned which may include:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Email production including: content layout, landing page construction, QA process etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing all data information and ensuring client-facing data dashboards are fully up-to-date&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take initiative to experiment, try new things, and bring fresh perspective to internal and external relationships in collaboration with teammates and senior staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as “point person” on multiple accounts leading the daily internal and external account management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managers and directors are responsible for team coaching/development, department growth and overall expanding BCom&#39;s network of relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other responsibilities as requested&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose-driven work that our clients rely on us for every day is challenging and edgy. It can be stressful at times. We rely on a shared set

&lt;p&gt;BCom is an outcomes agency specializing in digital strategy, advocacy, and fundraising for foundations, nonprofits, campaigns, and mission-driven brands. As we expand our long-term nonprofit, advocacy, and impact partnerships, we&#39;re building a new business development function to support our next phase of growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a &lt;strong&gt;Director of Business Development &lt;/strong&gt;to join our Revenue team. This position is responsible for generating new revenue by identifying opportunities, building relationships, developing proposals, and securing new clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the business development pipeline from prospecting through contract execution, ensuring a healthy flow of qualified opportunities that support the company&#39;s growth goals. Partnering closely with senior leadership, you will align sales efforts with revenue targets, market opportunities, and company priorities while maintaining accountability for new business performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a strategic seller and hands-on business development leader, you will manage complex sales cycles, lead pitches, negotiate opportunities, and position BCom as a trusted partner for campaigns, causes, associations, nonprofits, and mission-driven organizations. This role is directly accountable for achieving new business revenue goals and driving the company&#39;s sales performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience, Skills, &amp;amp; Competency Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hard Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7 or more years of experience in business development, sales, client acquisition, or revenue generation within a marketing agency, consulting firm, communications firm, political organization, or related environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience selling consulting or professional services to foundations, nonprofits, advocacy organizations, associations, chambers, or other mission-driven organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated alignment with mission-driven work and organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success generating new business and closing high-value client engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing complex sales cycles from prospecting through contract execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing and managing sales pipelines and revenue forecasts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proposal development, presentation, negotiation, and closing skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of marketing, communications, digital strategy, fundraising, advertising, or agency services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen with the ability to identify growth opportunities, evaluate deal potential, and align solutions to client needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using CRM systems and sales pipeline management tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to analyze sales data and performance metrics to drive decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written communication skills with the ability to independently develop and edit proposals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience presenting to executive-level stakeholders and decision-makers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-informed and comfortable leveraging emerging technologies to improve pipeline management, research, and proposal development while maintaining a relationship-first approach to consultative selling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Soft Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional relationship builder who develops trust quickly with prospective clients and partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly persuasive communicator with strong presentation and storytelling skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker who identifies opportunities and converts them into business results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter who takes initiative and consistently drives activity without heavy oversight.&lt

&lt;p&gt;BCom is a fast-growing, digital-first marketing agency that amplifies purpose-driven ideas. We partner with campaigns, causes, and brands to do work that matters. From online fundraising to media, advertising, and creative, our team has raised millions of dollars, built coalitions, and won tough fights. We’re building something special and looking for top talent to help take it to the next level. As we work toward ambitious growth goals, we want driven, strategic thinkers who are committed to doing great work and building something meaningful together.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a&lt;strong&gt; Senior Web Designer &lt;/strong&gt;to lead the quality, consistency, and execution of digital experiences across campaigns, brands, and client engagements. This is a hands-on role focused on designing and building high-performance websites that bring creative vision to life through thoughtful UI and UX execution. In this role, you will own the full lifecycle of website development, from site mapping and wireframing in Figma to final build and launch in WordPress using a page builder, translating high-level creative direction into polished, interactive digital experiences. Partnering closely with the Art Director - Design and Creative Director while owning execution, you will ensure all websites are visually strong, intuitive to navigate, mobile responsive, accessible, and optimized for performance and conversion, collaborating with strategists, copywriters, designers, and account teams to deliver high-impact web solutions that align with client goals and drive results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At BCom, we take pride in delivering top-tier work while showing up for each other. With our mission at the forefront, we center honesty, collaboration, and meaningful relationships in everything we do. If you’re looking to grow with a team rooted in purpose and committed to impact, we would like to meet you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Areas of Responsibility&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UI/UX Design &amp;amp; Prototyping&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate abstract client goals and brand guidelines into intuitive sitemaps, wireframes, and user flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design high-fidelity website mockups and interactive prototypes in Figma, establishing the visual language for digital projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply modern UI/UX principles to ensure websites are user-friendly, accessible (WCAG standards), and responsive across all screen sizes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create web design systems, including button styles, typography hierarchies, page sections, and component libraries, to ensure consistency across pages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present design concepts to internal teams and clients, articulating the rationale behind layout and usability decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CMS Implementation &amp;amp; Build&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take approved designs and build them pixel-perfectly within WordPress using the Elementor page builder (or similar frameworks).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the technical setup of pages, including installing necessary plugins, configuring forms, and integrating third-party tools (CRMs, donation platforms).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with back-end developers on complex functionality, providing them with clear design assets and specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thorough Quality Assurance (QA) testing across browsers and devices to ensure the site functions flawlessly before launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Site Maintenance &amp;amp; Optimization&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute ongoing website updates, landing page creation, and content refreshes for existing clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot visual bugs, broken links, or layout shifts that occur after browser or plugin updates.&lt;/li&gt;
